title: Interactions of monotonic variables
body:
This PR completely refactors the code for monotonic effects to implement interactions of monotonic variables (see issue #239) Monotonic terms now make use of essentially the same mechanism as noise-free terms. That is `mo()` functions calls are extracted from the formula and replaced by appropiate Stan (or R) code.

In addition,  `extract_draws.btl` and `linear_predictor` were refactored to be more consistent with the rest of the package.

title: Feature issue 240
body: This PR implements all the functionality that comes with the **bridgesampling** package, which computes the marginal likelihood of models based on the posterior samples. In order for the marginal likelihoods to be correct, all constants have to be kept in the log-posterior. This is now (hopefully) achieved by replacing all `~` with `target +=` statements and renormalizing truncated priors. Relates to issue #240.

title: CAR models
body:
This PR implements conditional autoregressive (CAR) and instrinsic conditional autoregressive (ICAR) models using the exact sparse representation presented in the case study of @mbjoseph (https://github.com/mbjoseph/CARstan). 

Together with the implementation of SAR models, this PR should close issue #6.

I will leave this PR open for a few days in case someone wants to comment on it (always welcome).

title: Streamline formula
body:
This branch was orginally only to simplify certain aspects of formula storing and parsing but then excalated quickly to include a bunch of other stuff.

Main changes:
- Make specifiation of non-linear models (hopefully) more intuitive and deprecate argument `nonlinear`.
- Restructure `brmsformula` objects to avoid having to use attributes, which repeatedly caused trouble.
- Make handling of addition terms more transparent by exporting and documenting related functions.
- Remove many units tests of internal functions and add tests of user-facing functions instead. This should help adding new features in the future without having to fix many tests failing just because of some slight refactoring without any user-visible changes.

Other changes:
- Introduce new function `prior_` allowing to specify priors using one-sided formulas or `quote`.
- Pass priors to **Stan** directly without performing any checks by setting `check = FALSE` in `set_prior`.
- Introduce method `nsamples` to extract the number of posterior samples.
- Fix a few minor bugs related to the backwards compatibility of multivariate and related models fitted with **brms** < 1.0.0.

title: Add kappa to list of valid classes and family-specific docs.
body:
This allows us to use `set_prior` for the kappa parameter in the `von_mises` distribution, e.g.

```
set_prior('normal(50,1)', class = 'kappa')
```

Also added a short blurb for kappa in the docs, and did some nitpicky doc fixes ('it' -> 'is' in priors.R, and lowercase 'c' for 'credible intervals' in the readme).
